  "prompt": "Which kind of guitar should I buy as an amateur?",
  "response": "As an amateur guitarist, choosing the right guitar depends on your musical interests, budget, and the style of music you want to play. Here are some great options for beginners:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Acoustic Guitar**\n   - **Best for**: Beginners who want to learn the basics of guitar playing or play folk, pop, rock, or singer-songwriter styles.\n   - **Why**: Acoustic guitars are versatile, portable, and don\u2019t require additional equipment like amplifiers.\n   - **Recommendations**:\n     - Yamaha FG800\n     - Fender FA-115\n     - Epiphone DR-100\n\n---\n\n### 2. **Classical Guitar (Nylon-String Guitar)**\n   - **Best for**: Beginners interested in classical music, flamenco, or fingerstyle playing.\n   - **Why**: Nylon strings are softer on the fingers, making it easier for beginners to learn.\n   - **Recommendations**:\n     - Cordoba C5\n     - Yamaha C40\n     - La Patron Pro 100\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Electric Guitar**\n   - **Best for**: Beginners who want to play rock, blues, metal, or jazz.\n   - **Why**: Electric guitars have lighter strings and a slimmer neck, which can be easier for some beginners. However, you\u2019ll need an amplifier and accessories.\n   - **Recommendations**:\n     - Squier Bullet Stratocaster\n     - Epiphone Les Paul SL\n     - Yamaha Pacifica 012\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Acoustic-Electric Guitar**\n   - **Best for**: Beginners who want the flexibility of both acoustic and amplified sound.\n   - **Why**: These guitars can be played acoustically or plugged into an amplifier for performances.\n   - **Recommendations**:\n     - Fender FA-345CE\n     - Yamaha APX600\n     - Ibanez AEG12II\n\n---\n\n### **Tips for Choosing a Guitar as a Beginner**:\n1. **Budget**: Start with an affordable guitar (usually $150\u2013$300) to ensure quality without breaking the bank.\n2. **Comfort**: Choose a guitar that feels comfortable in your hands and is the right size for your body.\n3. **Sound**: Play or listen to the guitar to ensure you like the tone.\n4. **Brand Reputation**: Stick to reputable brands like Yamaha, Fender, Epiphone, or Ibanez for reliability.\n5. **Get it Set Up**: Even a beginner guitar can play well with a proper setup by a technician.\n\n---\n\nIf you\u2019re unsure, a **steel-string acoustic guitar** is a great starting point for most beginners. It\u2019s versatile, easy to find, and helps build finger strength and technique. If you\u2019re drawn to a specific genre, consider the type of guitar that aligns with it!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
